  "title": "Product Manager Lead",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>• Develop a product roadmap to deliver seamless onramp, offramp and settlement capabilities</p><p>for our global payment platform.</p><p>• Ideate and design payment and settlement solutions to meet business needs.</p><p>• Track key product metrics to measure platform performance and health.</p><p>• Integrate with bank partners and payment service providers to enhance our global payments</p><p>platform</p><p>• Stay updated with relevant regulatory changes and monitor crypto industry trends to</p><p>anticipate compliance requirements and potential risks.</p><p>• Build internal tools and workflow automations to enhance our operation efficiency.</p><p>• Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including compliance, engineering, legal,</p><p>operations, and quality assurance to work on product planning and development processes.</p><p>• Define clear product requirements and user stories, working closely with engineering and</p><p>design teams to ensure successful implementation.</p><p>Must Have:</p><p>• At least 8 years of product management experience designing and building global payment</p><p>platforms such as fiat to crypto onramp and offramp.</p><p>• Good understanding of crypto ecosystem and various types of payment related licenses from</p><p>global authorities.</p><p>• Excellent written and verbal communications skills in English and Chinese (Mandarin); ability</p><p>to translate strategy into clear and actionable plans for Product Development, Engineering,</p><p>Design and Marketing</p><p>• Logical thinking - demonstrating logical reasoning and critical thinking to analyze and</p><p>evaluate complex problems and situations</p><p>• High proficiency delving into the technical product, system and implementation details. Able</p><p>to engage with engineering beyond just product and user experience needs; willing to roll up</p><p>sleeves and design scalable and extensible solutions</p><p>• Data oriented - identifying, defining, tracking and acting upon impact metrics. Experience</p><p>identifying KPIs and working with engineering and analytics on instrumentation and</p><p>monitoring</p><p>• Experience leading cross functional teams to deliver complex projects with multiple</p><p>dependencies and constraints in a highly dynamic environment</p>",
